Security Testing Lab

[Kali Linux] --> Attack
[Windows/Linux VMs] <-- Target
[Host PC] <-- Control/Monitor
Tips for Efficiency

Allocate enough RAM but not all; leave host usable

Use dynamic disks to save space

Start 1‚Äì2 VMs at a time for performance testing

Keep OS templates to quickly clone new machines

11Ô∏è‚É£ Optional Automation

Use Vagrant for scripting VM creation

Use Ansible for configuration management

Automate snapshots, network settings, and package installations

12Ô∏è‚É£ Document Your Lab

Take screenshots of network topology and VM dashboards

Keep a README.md describing:

Lab purpose

VM OS & role

IP addresses & networking

Tools installed
